    "name": "Martin Milner (3)",
    "profile": "Martin John Milner (mjmilner) grew up in Liverpool, England, and Nova Scotia (Canada) and lived for years in Brighton and Manchester before moving to Potsdam, Germany in 2008. He has worked with Waterwheel (folk rock, Brighton c.1989-92), One Big Party (reggae pop, Brighton, c. 1990-93), Guy Piran (Brighton, folk singer songwriter, c. 1990-93), Beverly Martyn (ran the Sweet Honesty folk club in Hove with Beverly c. 1993-4, performed at Bunjies Coffee House, London, 1994), Cuchillo (Manchester 1999-2000, latin jazz soul funk), Nadia Blue (Manchester, singer-songwriter Nadia Drew with Larry Gott and others, c.2005), Kokoriko (Manchester 2006-08, Afro-jazz funk with Serge Tebu and others), Aidan Jolly (Manchester, recorded 'State of Hysteria' 2008 with Aidan, Jaydev Mistry, Jilah Bakhshayesh), The Pedagawgs (rock and pop covers band, Potsdam/Berlin, 2008-current), The Martin Milner Orchestra (Potsdam, 2009-2015), The Need (Potsdam, 2023-current). mjmilner also performs solo. ",
